[2] China ex South Korea, suspected - media report
Date: 28 May 2015
Source: China.org / Xinhua
http://www.china.org.cn/china/Off_the_Wire/2015-05/28/content_35685240.htm


S China reports 1st suspected case of imported MERS
-----------------------------
South China's Guangdong Province reported its 1st suspected case of Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS), the National Health and Family Planning Commission announced on Thursday [28 May 2015].

A South Korean believed infected with the deadly virus came to China for a business trip on Tuesday [26 May 2015]. He has family members who are infected and had close contact with them back in Korea.

The 44-year-old man expressed discomfort as early as [21 May 2015] and reported fever of 38.7 degree celsius on Monday [25 May 2015]. He landed in Hong Kong on Tuesday [26 May 2015] and went on to Huizhou city in Guangdong Province via Shenzhen.

Health authorities put the man under observation in isolation and notified the World Health Organization on Wednesday [27 May 2015].

Of 35 known close contacts with man, no anomalies have been found so far.

MERS is a respiratory illness caused by a new type of coronavirus. The 1st case was identified in Saudi Arabia in 2012. There is no vaccine or treatment for the disease, with its fatality rate reaching 40.7 percent.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Another media report mentioned "Chinese state broadcaster CCTV said that authorities in Guangdong province found the Korean man on Thursday [28 May 2015] and isolated him in a hospital for treatment. They also isolated 35 people who had come in close contact with him, though none has yet to show symptoms." (http://www.cbc.ca/news/health/mers-suspect-case-in-south-korea-travelled-to-china-1.3091050).

From the unfolding picture, it appears as though there may have been significant spread of the MERS-CoV in South Korea related to the importation from the Middle East. At present it appears as though there are now 7 confirmed cases and another suspected case. One of the newly diagnosed cases today in the 1st report above is disturbing as the individual was not noted to have had close contact with either the index case or the index cases roommate. We await further information of results of epidemiologic studies. There have been discussions in the scientific community since the identification of the MERS-CoV of concern for the appearance of superspreaders... while there may have been superspreaders involved in some of the earlier KSA related nosocomial outbreaks, this current situation in South Korea may involve a superspreader, or better stated, superspreading event(s). That being said, one will not be surprised if there are more cases confirmed in the coming days.

The HealthMap/ProMED map of South Korea can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3393353,195. - Mod.MPP


